snippet.textDisplay: Using anesthesia at the dentist is usually rare. I am autistic and was terrified at the dentist and would beg for it. I am fifty and in my entire life with teeth, I got it once that was called twilight and once for the complete removal of my teeth from bad enamel. I am curious if people asked him for anesthesia or he just offered it. If Medicaid covers it, and the patient asked for it, would that still be fraud? You can't force someone to get put under for a tooth pulling. And if he can get in trouble for offering anesthesia to make a few extra dollars then what about those drug recovery places I saw on a documentary that bill Medicaid and other insurances for extra urine tests and so on? That seems more like fraud. Also, my Dad was a motorcycle stunt guy and he never wrecked, he knew what he was doing. I am sure the dentist wouldn't have done that if he wasn't positive of his footing. He sounds like a fun and caring dentist to me. Wish he was my dentist 😔. I'll be sending well wishes and Prayers to him. This seems truly like a witch Hunt and only his head will be accepted.
